benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/search/{searchKey} - Search custom fields

covered: GET Method: Valid Request scenarios covered (happy path, with required path parameter).
GET Method: Empty Response handling covered (no matches).
Query Parameters: Multiple valid parameter combinations tested (limit, offset, audit).
Pagination: Several tests cover limit/offset behavior and boundary values (TC02, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC28).
Authorization: Tests cover missing/invalid tokens (TC15, TC16).
Error Handling: Tests for invalid parameter formats and values (TC11, TC12, TC13, TC14).
Unsupported HTTP Method: Test for method not allowed (TC30).
Complex Scenarios: Audit parameter variations (TC03, TC04, TC05, TC28) and default parameter combinations (TC29).
Negative/Edge Scenarios: Tests for no matches (TC06), large datasets (TC19), and special cases (TC18, TC21, TC22, TC23, TC24, TC25, TC26, TC27).
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests validating behavior under rapid or burst requests (throttling, quotas).
Caching Behavior: No tests to verify caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or caching semantics.
Performance/Stress: Basic stress test exists (TC19) but deeper performance/rate-limiting assessments are missing.
Auditing/Compliance: Some tests assume audit fields present/absent but deeper verification across all audit levels and combinations could be expanded (beyond FULL/MINIMAL/NONE).
recommendations: Add explicit rate-limiting and throttling tests (e.g., high-concurrency scenarios, burst requests) and verify server-side throttling behavior.
Add caching validation tests to ensure proper headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache invalidation behavior.
Enhance performance testing with more structured stress tests under different data volumes and stable thresholds, including concurrent access patterns.
Extend audit-related scenarios to cover more combinations (e.g., audit with pagination + FULL/MINIMAL/NONE) and verify audit data consistency across edge cases.
